summary: Wow, just wow. I supported the CR kickstarter day one and now I'm considering deleting my pledge. I don't even use minis because...
body:
Wow, just wow. I supported the CR kickstarter day one and now I’m considering deleting my pledge. I don’t even use minis because I play online, by I try to support CR whenever I can. Now with the whole Limited Vax con exclusive debacle I’m kinda over the novelty.

I know they said they are going to try and make things right. We’ll see. I have a feeling that will only mean opening the preorders up to overseas GenCon-goers, but I am quite the cynic.

I’m just flabbergasted that they could make such a misstep. So many comments in the Kickstarter were begging for stretch goals and even when the Critters pledge $1.2 million their “surprise” is an announcement for an exclusive mini most of them will never see. They HAD another mini waiting in the wings for what?

What a way to end a kickstarter. /s
